API topic.  The way this is currently used is like:

```
listers.ResourceIndexer[*v1.FooBar]
```

In particular, the `*` is part of the type argument.  Could/should we simplfy that into:

```
listers.ResourceIndexer[v1.FooBar]
```

...which uses the actual type name, not the pointer.  Then signatures like:

```
func (l ResourceIndexer[T]) List(selector labels.Selector) (ret []*T, err error) {
  // ...
}

func (l ResourceIndexer[T]) Get(name string) (*T, error) {
  // ...
}
```

I personally find this more natural, but I have been known to get a bit too familiar with generics.

