comment_text:
The bug today is that a new field with a default value gets considered by kubelet as a change, so it restarts all pods (and all nodes do this roughly in sync).  #124220  fixes that, so a new default should not trigger a restart.

> this field should be an OS dependent field

OK, thast may still be true, but adding a default will avoid code like:

```
if windows {
  return doSomethingElse()
}
policy = merge // hardcoded default
if FSGroupChangePolicy == nil {
    policy = *FSGroupChangePolicy
}
return doSomethingWithPolicy(policy)
```

And when users `kubectl get` the pods they will see "Merge" instead of nothing

