comment_text:
The usual pattern is to initialize this, then (below) do something like:

```
opts.AllowPodLifecycleSleepActionZeroValue = opts.AllowPodLifecycleSleepActionZeroValue || lifecycleSleepZeroUsed(podSpec)
```

Where:

```
func lifecycleSleepZeroUsed(spec *api.PodSpec) bool {
    for i := range spec.containers {
        c := &spec.Containers[i]
        if c.Lifecycle != nil {
            if c.Lifecycle.PostStart != nil && c.Lifecycle.PostStart.Sleep != nil && c.Lifecycle.PostStart.Sleep.Seconds == 0 {
                return true
            }
            if c.Lifecycle.PreStop != nil && c.Lifecycle.PreStop.Sleep != nil && c.Lifecycle.PreStop.Sleep.Seconds == 0 {
                return true
            }
        }
    }
    return false
}
```

There's a util function somewhere, I can't recall the name, that lets you easily repeat this for spec.Containers, .EphemeralContainers, and .InitContainers.  You should use that.

This allows us to respect existing pods which have set this value.  See https://github.com/kubernetes/community/blob/master/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/feature-gates.md for more

